[start section id="20102"]

Mr. Trahan is a 77-year-old gentleman who is seen today at the request of Dr. Gates regarding his stage 3 carcinoma of the cecum.

[end section id="20102"]

[start section id="20103"]

I reviewed and confirm the history and physical examination as per Susan Samuels's note of April 13, 2010.
1.  April 7, 2010 - Presented to Elko Center for a general medical exam and noted to have iron-deficiency anemia.
2.  April 9, 2010 - Underwent first ever colonoscopy identifying a large ulcerating cecal mass.  Biopsies confirmed adenocarcinoma.  CT imaging of the abdomen and pelvis showed large regional lymph nodes, no evidence of distant metastasis.  Chest x-ray negative.
3.  April 12, 2010 - Taken by Dr. Gates for a laparoscopic right hemicolectomy identifying a 8.8 x 5.3 x 2.8-cm mass in the ascending colon, grade 3 adenocarcinoma, negative surgical margins involving 13 of 45 regional lymph nodes.
Mr. Trahan is recovering from his surgery and doing well.

[end section id="20103"]

